text: The Catskill Park is in the Catskill Mountains in New York in the United States. It is made up of of land inside in four counties: Delaware, Greene, Sullivan, and Ulster. As of 2005, or 41 percent of the land within, is owned by the state as part of the Forest Preserve. Another 5% is owned by New York City. ==References== Category:Parks in the United States Category:Geography of New York (state)
